<figureCitation id="19193879529B91CEFD27E13AF102E649" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Adult males of the new species: lateral habitus, head (anterior view), head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (ventral view of left one in D dorsal view of right one in I), and fore leg (right one, inner view) A-E Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10122) F-J C. liae Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10485). Scale bars: 1.0 mm except for B, E, G and J (0.5 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453261" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Figures 3A-E</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="A9DDE8720B6704F8902B29E92981578D" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">, 4</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
