<subSubSection id="08D28B0B3D7DAE5DF28E98F0D527BCDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="61CE5FE60AA2FE7D1DFD49CE37E19DA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9C01E7492A345775A8636D4189CE865" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="BCBF7A079A323E5862BCFD64EB014851" genus="C." lsidName="C. longivalva" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" rank="species" species="longivalva">
<emphasis id="2D4FD8B36B5E2F4AF26BFEC863A8873A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">C. longivalva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in external morphology and structure of male genitalia, but can be distinguished from the latter by epandrium with short ventral lobe apically inlaid with a thick, long, inward-curved, spine-like seta (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3846CDDEBFAF3888F3EBA8B2B6DCFE52" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4A, B</figureCitation>
); surstylus with 2 small, peg-like sensilla on inner, apical surface, 2 tiny, tooth-like setae on inner, ventrosubapical surface, and 1 tiny, trichoid seta on inner, dorsosubapical surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03FD4C27DEEA20CB3E96F427BCB36FA4" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4C</figureCitation>
); and distal, narrow portion of oviscapt shorter than proximal, broad portion (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F0559B9BB72FCD993F80CB22B9201BBF" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="837F3B4907F543CBD5BC78E4E2D8EED4" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" type="description">
<paragraph id="30B4281DA4FBEBE36816AEC00290CAB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85EB27E626859CAE0C8B6D303A58DDF2" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
(♂, ♀). 
<emphasis id="F08E94145FAC0253007A82F7A69B25BC" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Head</emphasis>
: Supracervical setae about 17 per side. Dorsomedial arm of tentorial apodeme about 2/3 as long as dorsolateral arm. Eye red, somewhat roundish, lacking interfacetal setulae. Frontal vitta mat, black. First flagellomere not concave on inner margin. Facial carina trapeziform, medially twice as wide as first flagellomere, as long as pedicel and first flagellomere combined. Palpus convex on ventrodistal portion. Cibarium posterior sensilla minute, 1 or 2 per side. Labellum with 19 pseudotracheae per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E044B534F465F58AB9EC8F0D4867C43" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="FFC47146AD82E0D3C283854F279A8FD9" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C4E993CD84F92C1C1835AEAABD5E523F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Adult males of the new species: lateral habitus, head (anterior view), head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (ventral view of left one in D dorsal view of right one in I), and fore leg (right one, inner view) A-E Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10122) F-J C. liae Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10485). Scale bars: 1.0 mm except for B, E, G and J (0.5 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453261" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">3A, C</figureCitation>
): Scutum, scutellum and thoracic pleura glossy, blackish brown to black. Acrostichal setulae in 6 rows.
</paragraph>
<caption id="FAD84917807F1D3F6D2A7015F057E871" doi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453261" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="730CE728323EE3C93B915ECF1331BCB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="957C5792A4170845501B57C365611E5E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Adult males of the new species: lateral habitus, head (anterior view), head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (ventral view of left one in 
<emphasis id="054B01A581AA676A6163521003A62A37" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">D</emphasis>
dorsal view of right one in 
<emphasis id="D9000C10F2760A1B3D6BA32281194C2B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">I</emphasis>
), and fore leg (right one, inner view) 
<emphasis id="83B3794193BC518CE8499EBE763FCB49" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">A-E</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F5FBEB594D25A1B30857616F87F9B15E" authorityName="Jiao &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Colocasiomyia todai" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="todai">
<emphasis id="D594720495C027CEF5FE5E7130D36BC9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Colocasiomyia todai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. (#10122) 
<emphasis id="907BCABEAF23C1E86F0E242ADFDA8C90" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">F-J</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="94F9302E381571963E57EB5B446078B9" genus="C." lsidName="C. liae" pageId="0" pageNumber="127" rank="species" species="liae">
<emphasis id="4518A8EF03E09FBEC1494FEF9A06E696" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">C. liae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. (#10485). Scale bars: 1.0 mm except for 
<emphasis id="DA5F6F21181619A2AEBA02870AC34806" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">B</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="7DB927AF74856878C925DBE4E79F6F28" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">E</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="C27C3563D5899C5EEF89A8BA4992C935" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">G</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="9982832B6EFC552F5AEFB9DE9FC0E630" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">J</emphasis>
(0.5 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="81E0E92248CCB2A2C542FC7351912E95" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="F9BF5DEADDC909E1847AD67F4B9B23C4" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D9D872833C9A1FBC22D2DBA15005DD49" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Adult males of the new species: lateral habitus, head (anterior view), head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (ventral view of left one in D dorsal view of right one in I), and fore leg (right one, inner view) A-E Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10122) F-J C. liae Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10485). Scale bars: 1.0 mm except for B, E, G and J (0.5 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453261" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">3D</figureCitation>
) hyaline, veins yellow. Halter grayish brown except for grayish yellow stalk.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D7AB7F6D41D0E60580660892EA5D6E66" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="494009F12AE35240CC021C06DCF86517" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Legs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="794C8B7F5CCB83D002265954C372AFB0" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Adult males of the new species: lateral habitus, head (anterior view), head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (ventral view of left one in D dorsal view of right one in I), and fore leg (right one, inner view) A-E Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10122) F-J C. liae Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10485). Scale bars: 1.0 mm except for B, E, G and J (0.5 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453261" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">3A, E</figureCitation>
) blackish brown to black except for grayish yellow tarsi. Foreleg second tarsomere with 10-12 pegs. Foreleg coxa large, with 1-2 long setae on underside near attachment to trochanter. Small preapical dorsal seta present only on hindleg tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F486CB8B64BD68F06866DFD96CC3BC4E" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="597912DEE84655A299463F88C5BA4D85" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2B4B01743F46CFFE88F6DAD2C30CA64E" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Adult males of the new species: lateral habitus, head (anterior view), head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (ventral view of left one in D dorsal view of right one in I), and fore leg (right one, inner view) A-E Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10122) F-J C. liae Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. ( 10485). Scale bars: 1.0 mm except for B, E, G and J (0.5 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453261" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">3A</figureCitation>
): Tergites glossy, entirely black; II to VI+VII each bearing setulae and setae in approximately 3-4 transverse rows; setae of posteriomost row largest. Sternites yellowish brown to blackish brown; VI somewhat triangular, posteriorly not bilobed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5BA0B8DE3AFC8140E9124CB9DC325850" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="F6A2BFE0681DD7CCA2B88CF45FA40304" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Male terminalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="079724AE44F96E80E62247080A2F335A" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4A-E</figureCitation>
): Epandrium broad, with large, prominent apodeme lobe on anteromedial to subventral margin, pubescent except for anterior and ventral margins; anteroventral portion curved inward, apically articulated to lateral arm of hypandrium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A93DD26E10C7D167F99C4B89B1077D16" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4A, B</figureCitation>
). Cercus semilunar, narrowly projected at ventral apex, pubescent except for anterior margin and ventral 1/3, with ca 52 setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DEE13543FB8CF9536BC80CC27F9FDBDB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus entirely narrow sclerite, elongated downward, basally articulated with epandrial ventral lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4706AE40D88DD79E41327C092E5C7592" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4A-C</figureCitation>
). Tenth sternite less sclerotized, folded into two lateral lobes caudodorsally connected with each other (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3DB635FBCDCF0CCF1FED06222E68B995" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium long, thin plate, distal 1/3 constricted, posteriorly T-shaped, with lateral arms fused to aedeagal basal processes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="826D3DAC392A19421567A7F21AB9146D" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4D, E</figureCitation>
). Paramere broad sword-shaped in lateral view, coalescent to hypandrium, triangular in ventral view, distally curved ventrad, with ca 4 sensilla arranged in a row (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="363A3E7CF4F379B7C5F5A49C1A176858" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4D, E</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus separated into a pair of lobes ventrally connected with each other, pubescent basally, subapically bent ventrad, pointed at apex; aedeagal basal processes somewhat membranous, connecting dorsobasal corners of aedeagus and lateral arms of hypandrium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5B10D22A3B92EADD8C0C1E95E379DD4E" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Colocasiomyia todai Jiao &amp; Gao, sp. nov. Adult male (holotype  10122) and female (paratype,  10100) from Ertaipo, Gaoligong Mountains, Baoshan, Yunnan, China A periphallic organs (lateral view) B periphallic organs (ventral view) C surstylus (right one, inner view) D phallic organs (dorsal view) E phallic organs (lateral view) F oviscapt (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed = aedeagus, aed a = aedeagal apodeme, aed b p = aedeagal basal process, cerc = cercus, epand = epandrium, epand a = epandrial apodeme, hypd = hypandrium, pm = paramere, 10 S = tenth sternite. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.968.56677.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/453262" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">4D, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
